# ========================================
# EXCEPTIONS: Always Include These
# ========================================

# Allow specific configuration examples (without secrets)
!example.env
!config.example.json

# Allow README files everywhere
!README.md
!**/README.md

# Allow documentation
!*.md
!docs/**/*.md

# Allow MCP server documentation
!MCP\ Servers/**/*.md
!MCP\ Servers/**/README.md

# Allow template files
!**/templates/**
!**/*-template.*

# Allow .claude plugin system (no secrets here)
!.claude/plugin.json
!.claude/agents/**
!.claude/skills/**
!.claude/commands/**

# Allow specific safe data files for examples
!**/test-data/*.json
!**/examples/*.csv

# ========================================
# Security Notes
# ========================================

# If you accidentally commit sensitive data:
# 1. DO NOT just remove it in a new commit
# 2. Use git filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner
# 3. Force push to rewrite history
# 4. Rotate any exposed API keys immediately
# 5. Notify Mitchell Keller

# For more info: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/removing-sensitive-data-from-a-repository

